NAME
    user - Manage users
DESCRIPTION
    The USER command allows you to add, remove, and manage users on a Pythinux system.
SYNTAX
    user list
        Lists all users
    user add <username> <password> <group_name>
        Add a user.
    user remove <user>
        Remove a user.
    user info <user>
        View info about a user. NOTE: This information is unformatted and probably not useful to most people, as all the relevant info is in `user list`.
SEE ALSO
    group - manage groups
